In order to use the features available in eloquent, you first have to find the relationship between your models or tables.

The raltionship in laravel is based on two table one parent table and the other is child table.

for example a record in news table can belong to category. In this case News has one to one relation with category table.

So in the news model you have to define belongsto relationship inside category method. 

laravel will automatically......

Note: In order insert data into the linked table you have to define the mass assignable attributes inside related table.
e.g. protected $fillable = ['col-1',];
